pes</Type><Text>Parental supervision at all times is a must for younger children under 5 years as the layout of the camp is very open.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>DiningFacilities</Type><Text>This eco design lodge is in the form of a German fortress and the surrounding area is rich in World War I history. This establishment is ideal for business travellers and holidaymakers alike and offers modern facilities for the perfect conference in the wild. It offers a truly exclusive bush experience, being situated in the heart of the Taita Hills Wildlife Sanctuary. The sanctuary is a success story in sustainable conservation where wildlife thrive, including elephant, lion, buffalo and giraffes. The game drives are tightly controlled to ensure that animals are not harassed and some areas are completely closed to vehicles. This lodge comprises a total of 62 rooms including 9 singles and 2 apartments. Facilities on offer to guests at this air-conditioned establishment include a lobby area with a 24-hour reception, a hotel safe, a currency exchange facility, a TV lounge and a children's playground. Child-minding services are available on request. There is a cafe, a bar and a restaurant and guests will appreciate the conference facilities and wireless Internet access. There is a gift shop, a fuel station and business centre. They can also take advantage of the room and laundry services. Parking is available for those arriving by car.</Text></Description><Amenity><Code>CoffeeTeaMaker</Code><Text>Tea and Coffee maker</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Safe</Code><Text>Safe</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>HandicapAccessible</Code><Text>Handicap accessible</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>OutdoorPool</Code><Text>Outdoor swimming pool</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>RoomService</Code><Text>Room service</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>MoneyExchange</Code><Text>Money exchange</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Bar</Code><Text>Bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Publ